  "text": "In this work, we focus on the non-unique winner model to keep the proofs as simple as possible. All our results still hold for the unique winner model. Our proofs can easily be adapted for this model, e.g. by adding a tie-breaking voter who initially votes for p, cf. Faliszewski et al. [CITATION_1] , or some similar adjustment. Note that in general, tie-breaking is not an easy task and an interesting question of its own [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
